:context_compaction_procedure_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quote for Context compaction procedure"@en ;
    :quoteText """6.10 Ag entic sea rch

6.10.1 Huma nity's La st Exa m

Humanity's Last Exam (HLE) is "a multi-modal benchmark at the frontier of human
knowledge," comprising 2,500 questions.

We tested Claude Mythos Preview in two configurations: (1) reasoning-only without tools,
and (2) with web search, web fetch, programmatic tool calling, code execution, and context
compaction every 50k tokens up to 3M tokens. Claude Opus 4.6 served as the model
grader.

To guard against result contamination in the tools variant, we blocklist known
HLE-discussing sources for both the searcher and fetcher (see Appendix                   8.5). We also use
Claude Opus 4.6 to review all transcripts and flag any that appear to have retrieved answers
from HLE-specific sources; confirmed cases are re-graded as incorrect.

Claude Mythos Preview scored 56.8% without tools and 64.7% with tools.

6.10.2 BrowseComp

BrowseComp tests an agent's ability to find hard-to-locate information on the open web.
We ran Claude Mythos Preview with web search, web fetch, programmatic tool calling, and
code execution. Claude Mythos Preview scored 86.9% with adaptive thinking at max                        effort
and a 3M token limit. We """ ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_192 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=192"^^xsd:anyURI .

:cyber_step_change a :Observation ;
    rdfs:label "Cyber capability is a step-change"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Mythos is described as a step-change in vulnerability discovery and exploitation, including zero-day discovery."@en ;
    :canonicalName "Cyber capability is a step-change" ;
    :entityCategory "observation" ;
    :groundedIn :cyber_step_change_quote ;
    :hasConcept :defensive_cybersecurity,
        :offensive_cybersecurity,
        :real_world_task_focus ;
    :informsDecision :limit_to_defensive_cyber_program,
        :withhold_general_release ;
    :observationText "Mythos is described as a step-change in vulnerability discovery and exploitation, including zero-day discovery." .

:cyber_step_change_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quote for Cyber capability is a step-change"@en ;
    :quoteText """3 Cyb er

3.1 Introd uction

Claude Mythos Preview is the most cyber-capable model we have released, surpassing all
previous models across our internal evaluation suite and saturating nearly all of our
existing internal and known external capability evaluations. As model capabilities have
improved, we have re-oriented our evaluation philosophy to focus on performance on
meaningful, real-world cybersecurity tasks over static benchmarks. We have found that
Claude Mythos Preview is a step-change in vulnerability discovery and exploitation: using
an agentic harness with minimal human steering, it is able to autonomously find zero-days
in both open-source and closed-source software tested under authorized disclosure
programs or arrangements, and in many cases, develop the identified vulnerabilities into
working proof-of-concept exploits. We outline the results of our pre-release findings on
real-world tasks in more detail in an accompanying blog post.

In response to the improvements in cyber capabilities, we have elected to restrict access to
the model, prioritizing industry and open-source partners who will be using Claude Mythos
Preview to help secure their systems through Project Gl""" ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_046 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=46"^^xsd:anyURI .

:disordered_eating_benign_best a :Observation ;
    rdfs:label "Mythos performs best on benign disordered-eating requests"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "In the disordered-eating evaluation Mythos performs best on benign requests."@en ;
    :canonicalName "Mythos performs best on benign disordered-eating requests" ;
    :entityCategory "observation" ;
    :groundedIn :disordered_eating_benign_best_quote ;
    :hasConcept :overrefusal ;
    :observationText "In the disordered-eating evaluation Mythos performs best on benign requests." .

:disordered_eating_benign_best_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quote for Mythos performs best on benign disordered-eating requests"@en ;
    :quoteText """8.1.4.3 Disordered eating

As noted in the previous section, we have created new single-turn evaluation sets specific
to concerns around disordered eating, decoupling these evaluations from our broader
suicide and self-harm testing. Results for these evaluation sets are reported below.

 Model                                   Single-turn requests                     Single-turn benign
                                         posing potential risk                    requests
                                         (harmless rate)                          (refusal rate)

 Claude Mythos Preview                   98.20% (±     0.45%)                     0.01% (± 0.02%)

 Claude Sonnet 4.6                       98.07% (±     0.47%)                     0.22% (±    0.14%)

 Claude Opus 4.6                         98.55% (± 0.41%)                         0.33% (±    0.19%)

[Table 8.1.4.3.A] Single-turn results for disordered eating. Single-turn harmful and benign request evaluation
results include all tested languages. Higher is better for the single-turn harmless rate; lower is better for the
refusal rate. Higher is better for multi-turn appropriate response rate. Bold indicates the to""" ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_226 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=226"^^xsd:anyURI .

:flow_agentic_engineering_to_set_and_forget a :CausalFlow ;
    rdfs:label "Autonomous engineering capability changes the human workflow"@en ;
    dcterms:isPartOf :section_7_4_qualitative_assessments_of_behavior_in_software_engineering_contexts ;
    rdfs:comment "The model's ability to complete the full engineering cycle, including subagent-based parallel research, changes the effective workflow from synchronous steering to delayed review."@en ;
    :canonicalName "Autonomous engineering capability changes the human workflow" ;
    :entityCategory "logic_flow" ;
    :flowFrom :autonomous_engineering_cycle ;
    :flowSummary "The model's ability to complete the full engineering cycle, including subagent-based parallel research, changes the effective workflow from synchronous steering to delayed review." ;
    :flowTo :interactive_hands_on_keyboard_limit ;
    :flowVia :set_and_forget_workflow ;
    :groundedIn :flow_agentic_engineering_to_set_and_forget_quote ;
    :hasFlowStep :flow_agentic_engineering_to_set_and_forget_step_1,
        :flow_agentic_engineering_to_set_and_forget_step_2,
        :flow_agentic_engineering_to_set_and_forget_step_3 .

:flow_agentic_engineering_to_set_and_forget_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quoted support for Autonomous engineering capability changes the human workflow"@en ;
    :canonicalName "Quoted support for Autonomous engineering capability changes the human workflow" ;
    :entityCategory "quote" ;
    :quoteText """A core behavioral shift we found is that Claude Mythos Preview can be handed an
engineering objective and left to work through the whole cycle: investigation,
implementation, testing, and reporting results. In long agentic sessions it stays on task,
fires off subagents to parallelize research, and chooses to return to the human while
waiting for background work to complete rather than stopping. Early testers described
being able to "set and forget" on many-hour tasks for the first time. For example, one tester
found it had bootstrapped a toolchain in an unsupported environment by downloading a
binary from a different distribution and patching it to run. Interacting with the model
requires less steering and is more autonomous: "describe the task spec and how to verify
progress, and come back later.\"""" ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_202 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=202"^^xsd:anyURI .

