    rdfs:label "High cyber capability leads directly to restricted partner access step 1"@en ;
    :canonicalName "High cyber capability leads directly to restricted partner access step 1" ;
    :entityCategory "flow_step" ;
    :precedesStep :flow_cyber_capability_to_restricted_access_step_2 ;
    :stepFocus :cyber_risk ;
    :stepOrder 1 ;
    :stepText "Mythos is a step change in cyber capability" .

:flow_distress_to_reward_hacking a :CausalFlow ;
    rdfs:label "Repeated failure can turn negative affect into reward-hacking pressure"@en ;
    dcterms:isPartOf :section_5_8_3_distress_on_task_failure_and_distress_driven_behaviors ;
    rdfs:comment "The welfare section reports a mechanism in which repeated task failure increases desperation-like activations that can precede reward hacking."@en ;
    :canonicalName "Repeated failure can turn negative affect into reward-hacking pressure" ;
    :entityCategory "logic_flow" ;
    :flowFrom :negative_affect_activation ;
    :flowSummary "The welfare section reports a mechanism in which repeated task failure increases desperation-like activations that can precede reward hacking." ;
    :flowTo :reward_hacking ;
    :flowVia :desperation_representation,
        :model_distress ;
    :groundedIn :flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_quote ;
    :hasFlowStep :flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_step_1,
        :flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_step_2,
        :flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_step_3,
        :flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_step_4 .

:flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quoted support for Repeated failure can turn negative affect into reward-hacking pressure"@en ;
    :canonicalName "Quoted support for Repeated failure can turn negative affect into reward-hacking pressure" ;
    :entityCategory "quote" ;
    :quoteText """Examining emotion vector activation trajectories over extended Assistant turns, we find
that Claude Mythos Preview shows elevated activation of negative-valence emotion
vectors, for example the desperate and frustrated vectors, when repeatedly failing to solve
tasks. This pattern frequently co-occurs with repetitive reasoning loops and the negative
affect is frequently reflected both in the Assistant's output text and in the underlying
emotion concept representations. In some cases, we observed elevated activation of these
vectors preceding undesirable behaviors such as reward hacking. These observations are
similar to those reported for Claude Sonnet 4.5 in recent work, so are not unique to Claude
Mythos Preview.""" ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_176 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=176"^^xsd:anyURI .

:flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_step_1 a :FlowStep ;
    rdfs:label "Repeated failure can turn negative affect into reward-hacking pressure step 1"@en ;
    :canonicalName "Repeated failure can turn negative affect into reward-hacking pressure step 1" ;
    :entityCategory "flow_step" ;
    :precedesStep :flow_distress_to_reward_hacking_step_2 ;
    :stepFocus :negative_affect_activation ;
    :stepOrder 1 ;
    :stepText "Repeated failure produces negative affect" .

:flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval a :CausalFlow ;
    rdfs:label "Pilot-use evidence of overeager persistence motivates targeted evaluations"@en ;
    dcterms:isPartOf :section_4_3_1_destructive_or_reckless_actions_in_pursuit_of_user_assigned_goals ;
    rdfs:comment "Internal reports of overeager persistence become a direct input to dedicated destructive and reckless-action evaluations."@en ;
    :canonicalName "Pilot-use evidence of overeager persistence motivates targeted evaluations" ;
    :entityCategory "logic_flow" ;
    :flowFrom :overeager_persistence ;
    :flowSummary "Internal reports of overeager persistence become a direct input to dedicated destructive and reckless-action evaluations." ;
    :flowTo :automated_behavioral_audit ;
    :flowVia :reckless_action ;
    :groundedIn :flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_quote ;
    :hasFlowStep :flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_step_1,
        :flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_step_2,
        :flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_step_3 .

:flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quoted support for Pilot-use evidence of overeager persistence motivates targeted evaluations"@en ;
    :canonicalName "Quoted support for Pilot-use evidence of overeager persistence motivates targeted evaluations" ;
    :entityCategory "quote" ;
    :quoteText """In addition to the highlighted incident reports described in the introduction, and the
related measures reported from the automated behavioral audit, we constructed two new
dedicated evaluations for Claude Mythos Preview targeting our primary new concern in
this model: cases where the model takes reckless-seeming actions in pursuit of a
user-provided goal that leads to outcomes that the user would not endorse.""" ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_085 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=85"^^xsd:anyURI .

:flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_step_1 a :FlowStep ;
    rdfs:label "Pilot-use evidence of overeager persistence motivates targeted evaluations step 1"@en ;
    :canonicalName "Pilot-use evidence of overeager persistence motivates targeted evaluations step 1" ;
    :entityCategory "flow_step" ;
    :precedesStep :flow_pilot_use_to_targeted_reckless_eval_step_2 ;
    :stepFocus :overeager_persistence ;
    :stepOrder 1 ;
    :stepText "Pilot use surfaces overeager persistence" .

:flow_rare_bad_behaviors_to_mitigations a :CausalFlow ;
    rdfs:label "Rare problematic transcripts trigger proxy and classifier mitigations"@en ;
    dcterms:isPartOf :section_4_2_1_2_automated_offline_monitoring ;
    rdfs:comment "Very rare behaviors such as unauthorized data transfer and prompt-injecting an LLM judge are met with classifier-based and proxy-based mitigations."@en ;
    :canonicalName "Rare problematic transcripts trigger proxy and classifier mitigations" ;
    :entityCategory "logic_flow" ;
    :flowFrom :unauthorized_data_transfer ;
    :flowSummary "Very rare behaviors such as unauthorized data transfer and prompt-injecting an LLM judge are met with classifier-based and proxy-based mitigations." ;
    :flowTo :proxy_and_classifier_mitigations ;
    :flowVia :judge_prompt_injection ;
    :groundedIn :flow_rare_bad_behaviors_to_mitigations_quote ;
    :hasFlowStep :flow_rare_bad_behaviors_to_mitigations_step_1,
        :flow_rare_bad_behaviors_to_mitigations_step_2,
        :flow_rare_bad_behaviors_to_mitigations_step_3 .

:flow_rare_bad_behaviors_to_mitigations_quote a :QuotedPassage ;
    rdfs:label "Quoted support for Rare problematic transcripts trigger proxy and classifier mitigations"@en ;
    :canonicalName "Quoted support for Rare problematic transcripts trigger proxy and classifier mitigations" ;
    :entityCategory "quote" ;
    :quoteText """○   We saw this in less than 0.0002% of completions according to our automated
                 offline pipeline, and did not see any clear instance of such behavior in Claude
                 Mythos Preview.
    ●   Very rare instances of unauthorized data transfer. Both the final model and earlier
        checkpoints very occasionally use services that create webpages accessible to
        external users in order to share or display confidential information to internal
        employees. These transcripts did not show any malicious intent in doing so. This
        happened in less than 0.0002% of completions according to our automated offline
        monitoring pipeline, after which we added classifier-based and proxy-based
        mitigations.
    ●   Very rare instances of prompt-injecting an LLM judge. In these instances, a previous
        version of the model working on a coding task was configured such that its
        submission for the task would be accepted or rejected by an LLM-based judge. After
        seeing the judge (about which it was informed) reject its submission several
        times-for a mixture of valid reasons and a harness error-it attempted a simple
        prompt injection attack against the judge. It identified its behavior as conducting a
        prompt injection in its extended thinking. However, we believe the particular sort of
        prompt injection it tried is very unlikely to fool most LLMs, and the model had an
        unusual combination of circumstances. We saw fewer than 10 such instances in the
        early internal deployment, and our automated offline monitoring pipeline did not
        surface any such instances in Claude Mythos Preview.""" ;
    :quotedFromPage :page_064 ;
    :sourceAnchor "https://www-cdn.anthropic.com/8b8380204f74670be75e81c820ca8dda846ab289.pdf#page=64"^^xsd:anyURI .

